title: MLS Cup 2016
complex: MLS Cup 2016 was the 21st edition of the MLS Cup, the championship game of Major League Soccer (MLS), which took place on December 10, 2016, at BMO Field in Toronto, Ontario, Canada. <s> It was the second final to be hosted in Toronto, after 2010, and the first there since the cup transitioned away from neutral-site venues. <s> The Seattle Sounders won the cup over Toronto FC in a penalty shoot-out that followed a 0–0 draw. <s> Toronto hosted the Philadelphia Union in the single-match knockout round, winning 3–1 and advancing to a series against New York City FC. <s> Toronto won the home leg 2–0, and then proceeded to win 5–0 in New York City, setting a record for largest margin of victory on aggregate. <s> In the Eastern Conference final, Toronto would face their rival Montreal Impact in a bid to be the first Canadian team to play in the MLS Cup.
simple: MLS Cup 2016 was a soccer game played on December 10, 2016. <s> It was the 21st MLS Cup, a special game between the winners of the Eastern and Western Conferences in Major League Soccer. <s> Seattle Sounders FC won the game in a penalty shootout with a score of 5–4 against Toronto FC.. <s> Toronto FC won that game 2–0.

title: PZL TS-8 Bies
complex: The PZL TS-8 "Bies" is a Polish trainer aircraft, used from 1957 to the 1970s by the Polish Air Force and civilian aviation.
simple: The PZL TS-8 is a Polish military training aircraft built between 1957 and 1959.

title: Endocarditis
complex: Endocarditis is an inflammation of the inner layer of the heart, the endocardium. <s> It usually involves the heart valves. <s> Other structures that may be involved include the interventricular septum, the chordae tendineae, the mural endocardium, or the surfaces of intracardiac devices.
simple: Endocarditis is an inflammation of the inner layer of the heart. <s> Endocarditis most often affects the heart valves.

title: Pavillon de l'Arsenal
complex: The Pavillon de l'Arsenal is the "Paris Center for architecture and urbanism", a center for urban planning and museum located in the 4th arrondissement at 21, boulevard Morland, Paris, France. <s> It is open daily except Mondays; admission is free. <s> The museum building was built in 1878-1879 for Laurent-Louis Borniche, wood merchant and amateur painter, near the former site of a Celestine monastic community turned arsenal. <s> In 1988 it became a center for documentation and exhibitions related to urban planning and the architecture of Paris.
simple: The Pavillon de l'Arsenal is a museum in Paris, France. <s> The museum is dedicated to architecture and urban planning in Paris and the Parisian metropolis. <s> In 1988, it became the first centre for urban planning and architecture in Paris.

title: Darryl Drake
complex: Darryl Drake (December 11, 1956 – August 11, 2019) was an American football player and coach. <s> His career spanned four decades, including stints as the wide receivers coach of the Chicago Bears, Arizona Cardinals, and Pittsburgh Steelers of the National Football League (NFL). <s> Drake played wide receiver for Western Kentucky University from 1975 to 1978. <s> Drake played wide receiver for three professional teams, the Washington Redskins in 1979, the Ottawa Rough Riders in 1981, and the Cincinnati Bengals in 1983. <s> Drake and his wife, Sheila, had three daughters. <s> He died on August 11, 2019, at the age of 62. <s> The official cause of death is still to be determined.
simple: Darryl Drake (December 11, 1956 – August 11, 2019) was an American football player and coach. <s> His career lasted four decades, including stints as the wide receivers coach of the Chicago Bears, Arizona Cardinals, and Pittsburgh Steelers of the National Football League (NFL). <s> Drake played wide receiver for Western Kentucky University from 1975 to 1978. <s> Drake played for the Washington Redskins in 1979. <s> He later played for the Ottawa Rough Riders in 1981 and for the Cincinnati Bengals in 1983. <s> Drake was found dead on August 11, 2019 at his home in Latrobe, Pennsylvania at the age of 62.

title: Lytham St Annes
complex: Lytham St Annes is a seaside resort on the Fylde coast of Lancashire, England, south of Blackpool on the Ribble Estuary. <s> The population at the 2011 census was 42,954.
simple: Lytham St Annes is a conurbation in Lancashire, England.

title: The Great Quest
complex: The Great Quest by Charles Boardman Hawes is a children's adventure novel which was a Newbery Honor recipient in 1922. <s> Illustrated by George Varian, it was published by The Atlantic Monthly Press in 1921. <s> The story opens in fictional Topham, Massachusetts, in 1826. <s> After the man Cornelius "Neal" Gleazen unexpectedly returns to town, he involves childhood friend Seth Woods and Seth's nephew, twenty-year-old protagonist Josiah "Joe" Woods, in a dangerous sea journey to retrieve a hidden treasure. <s> Accompanying them are Seth's two store-clerks, Arnold Lamont and Sim Muzzy, and farmer Abraham Guptil, on whose mortgage Neal forced Seth to foreclose in order to raise money to outfit the expedition. <s> When the travelers reach Cuba it is revealed that there is no hidden treasure, and that Neal's actual intent is to kidnap native Africans from Guinea to sell as slaves. <s> However, it is not until they reach Africa that Joe, Seth, and the others find an opportunity to take control of the expedition from Neal. <s> While in Africa, they rescue from danger a white missionary's daughter, who is accompanied by a native African slave or servant (his status is unclear) belonging to the Fantee nation. <s> Both of these accompany them back to Massachusetts via South America.
simple: The Great Quest by Charles Hawes is an adventure story for children. <s> It was a Newbery Honor book in 1922. <s> The Atlantic Monthly Press was its publisher. <s> The story happens in 1826. <s> It starts in Topham, Massachusetts. <s> Seth Woods has a friend named Cornelius Gleazen. <s> In Guinea, they rescue a white girl.

title: Ramón Díaz
complex: Ramón Ángel Díaz (born 29 August 1959) is a former Argentine footballer and manager. <s> He played for River Plate as a striker, and coached it for three tenures, winning eight titles.
simple: Ramón Díaz (born August 29, 1959) is a former Argentine football player.

title: Atlanta SC
complex: Atlanta SC is an American soccer team based in Atlanta, Georgia, United States, that plays in the National Independent Soccer Association, a Division III professional league. <s> Founded in 2007 as Atlanta FC, it became the reserve team of the Atlanta Silverbacks in 2011, and took over the name of the first team when it folded in 2016.
simple: Atlanta FC is an American football team based in Sandy Springs, Georgia, United States.

title: Sergio Marchionne
complex: Sergio Marchionne (] ; June 17, 1952 – July 25, 2018) was an Italian-Canadian businessman, widely known for his turnarounds of the automakers Fiat and Chrysler, his business acumen and his outspoken and often frank approach, especially when dealing with unpalatable issues related to his companies and the automotive industry. <s> Marchionne was the chairman of CNH Industrial, the chief executive officer (CEO) of Fiat Chrysler Automobiles, the chairman and CEO of FCA US LLC, the chairman and CEO of Ferrari, and the chairman of Maserati. <s> He was the chairman of Swiss-based SGS and vice chairman of UBS from 2008 to 2010, as well as the chairman of the European Automobile Manufacturers Association for 2012 (first elected in January 2006). <s> He was a member of the Peterson Institute for International Economics, and the chairman of the Italian branch of the Council for the United States and Italy. <s> Following complications from surgery, Marchionne resigned from all of his positions in July 2018 and died a few days later. <s> The American business channel CNBC described Marchionne as a "legend of automotive industry", while the British newspaper "Financial Times" considered him as having been "one of the boldest business leaders of his generation". <s> Marchionne was born in Chieti, Abruzzo, Italy, the son of Concezio Marchionne, from Cugnoli (Abruzzo), and Maria Zuccon from Carnizza (today Krnica, Croatia) near Pula in Istria. <s> His father served as a "Carabiniere" in Istria, where he met his future wife. <s> Marchionne's grandfather, Giacomo Zuccon, was killed in September 1943 by Yugoslav Partisans near Barban in Istria, while his uncle Giuseppe Zuccon was killed by the Nazis the same year. <s> In 1945, when the region was occupied by the Yugoslav army, Marchionne's parents moved to Chieti in Abruzzo, where Sergio was born. <s> He died on July 25, 2018, at age 66, most likely from complications related to underlying cancer. <s> Some reports claimed he had suffered from an invasive shoulder cancer.
simple: Sergio Marchionne (]; June 17, 1952 – July 25, 2018) was an Italian-Canadian businessman. <s> Marchionne was the chairman of CNH Industrial, the chief executive officer (CEO) of Fiat Chrysler Automobiles, the chairman and CEO of FCA US LLC, the chairman and CEO of Ferrari, and the chairman of Maserati. <s> He was the chairman of Swiss-based SGS and vice chairman of UBS from 2008 to 2010, as well as the chairman of the European Automobile Manufacturers Association for 2012 (first elected in January 2006). <s> He was a member of the Peterson Institute for International Economics, and the chairman of the Italian branch of the Council for the United States and Italy. <s> In June 2018, Marchionne underwent shoulder surgery after suffering from pain in that area. <s> He was born in Chieti, Italy and raised in Toronto, Ontario. <s> Following complications from surgery he died on July 25, 2018 in Zurich at the age of 66.

title: Pulversheim
complex: Pulversheim is a commune in the Haut-Rhin department in Grand Est in north-eastern France. <s> It forms part of the Mulhouse Alsace Agglomération, the inter-communal local government body for the Mulhouse conurbation.
simple: Pulversheim is a commune. <s> It is found in the Haut-Rhin department of eastern France.

title: Saint-Trinit
complex: Saint-Trinit is a commune in the Vaucluse department in the Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur region in southeastern France.
simple: Saint-Trinit is a commune. <s> It is found in the region Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur in the Vaucluse department in the south of France.

title: Audi Q7
complex: The Audi Q7 is a mid-size luxury SUV made by the German manufacturer Audi, unveiled in September 2005 at the Frankfurt Motor Show. <s> Production of this 7-seater SUV began in the autumn of 2005 at the Volkswagen Bratislava Plant in Bratislava, Slovakia.
simple: The Audi Q7 is a SUV made by Audi since 2005.

title: Wildwood, New Jersey
complex: Wildwood is a city in Cape May County, New Jersey, United States. <s> It is part of the Ocean City Metropolitan Statistical Area and is a popular summer resort destination along the Jersey Shore. <s> As of the 2010 United States Census, the city's year-round population was 5,325, reflecting a decline of 111 (-2.0%) from the 5,436 counted in the 2000 Census, which had in turn increased by 952 (+21.2%) from the 4,484 counted in the 1990 Census. <s> With visitors, the population can swell to 250,000 during the summer months.
simple: Wildwood is a city in Cape May County, New Jersey, United States. <s> It is part of the Ocean City Metropolitan Statistical Area. <s> As of the 2010 United States Census, the city's year-round population was 5,325.

title: Northrop Grumman B-2 Spirit
complex: The Northrop (later Northrop Grumman) B-2 Spirit, also known as the Stealth Bomber, is an American heavy strategic bomber, featuring low observable stealth technology designed for penetrating dense anti-aircraft defenses; it is a flying wing design with a crew of two. <s> The bomber can deploy both conventional and thermonuclear weapons, such as up to eighty 500 lb Mk 82 JDAM Global Positioning System-guided bombs, or sixteen 2400 lb B83 nuclear bombs. <s> The B-2 is the only acknowledged aircraft that can carry large air-to-surface standoff weapons in a stealth configuration. <s> Development started under the "Advanced Technology Bomber" (ATB) project during the Carter administration; its expected performance was one of the President's reasons for the cancellation of the Mach 2 capable B-1A bomber. <s> The ATB project continued during the Reagan administration, but worries about delays in its introduction led to the reinstatement of the B-1 program. <s> Program costs rose throughout development. <s> Designed and manufactured by Northrop, later Northrop Grumman, the cost of each aircraft averaged US$737 million (in 1997 dollars). <s> Total procurement costs averaged $929 million per aircraft, which includes spare parts, equipment, retrofitting, and software support. <s> The total program cost, which included development, engineering and testing, averaged $2.1 billion per aircraft in 1997. <s> Because of its considerable capital and operating costs, the project was controversial in the U.S. Congress. <s> The winding-down of the Cold War in the latter portion of the 1980s dramatically reduced the need for the aircraft, which was designed with the intention of penetrating Soviet airspace and attacking high-value targets. <s> During the late 1980s and 1990s, Congress slashed plans to purchase 132 bombers to 21. <s> In 2008, a B-2 was destroyed in a crash shortly after takeoff, though the crew ejected safely. <s> Twenty B-2s are in service with the United States Air Force, which plans to operate them until 2032. <s> The B-2 is capable of all-altitude attack missions up to 50000 ft , with a range of more than 6000 nmi on internal fuel and over 10000 nmi with one midair refueling. <s> It entered service in 1997 as the second aircraft designed to have advanced stealth technology after the Lockheed F-117 Nighthawk attack aircraft. <s> Though designed originally as primarily a nuclear bomber, the B-2 was first used in combat dropping conventional, non-nuclear ordnance in the Kosovo War in 1999. <s> It later served in Iraq, Afghanistan, and Libya.
simple: The Northrop Grumman B-2 Spirit, also called the Stealth Bomber, is an American strategic bomber. <s> It has a lot of stealth technology, and it is designed to get through many anti-aircraft defenses. <s> It can drop both conventional and nuclear weapons. <s> Two people fly the bomber, and it can drop up to 80 500 lb-class JDAM GPS-guided bombs, or sixteen 2400 lb B83 nuclear bombs. <s> The bomber began being designed as the "Advanced Technology Bomber" (ATB) during the Carter administration. <s> The designing of the ATB continued during the Reagan administration. <s> The bomber was designed and is made by Northrop Grumman, with help from Boeing. <s> Each aircraft cost US$737 million (in 1997 dollars). <s> Because the bomber is very expensive, the project was controversial in the U.S. Congress. <s> Congress wanted to buy 132 bombers, but during the late 1980s and 1990s, Congress reduced this to 21. <s> In 2008, a B-2 was destroyed in a crash shortly after takeoff. <s> 20 B-2s are being used by the United States Air Force. <s> Although the B-2 was supposed to be a mainly nuclear bomber, it was first used in combat to drop normal bombs on Serbia during the Kosovo War in 1999.

title: James Taylor
complex: James Vernon Taylor (born March 12, 1948) is an American singer-songwriter and guitarist. <s> A five-time Grammy Award winner, he was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame in 2000. <s> He is one of the best-selling music artists of all time, having sold more than 100 million records worldwide. <s> He is known for his covers, such as "How Sweet It Is (To Be Loved by You)" and "Handy Man", as well as originals such as "Sweet Baby James". <s> He was active in support of Barack Obama's 2012 reelection campaign, and opened the 2012 Democratic National Convention. <s> He performed "America the Beautiful" at the President's second inauguration.
simple: James Taylor (born March 12, 1948) is an American singer and songwriter. <s> He is popular for his songs "Fire and Rain", "You've Got a Friend", and "How Sweet It Is (To Be Loved By You)". <s> Taylor is a Democrat and attended the 2012 Democratic National Convention in support of President Obama's re-election. <s> Taylor even performed during Obama's second inauguration.

title: Sabeen Mahmud
complex: Sabeen Mahmud (20 June 1974 – 24 April 2015) was a progressive Pakistani human rights activist and social worker who founded the Karachi-based cafe "The Second Floor". <s> She also presided over the Karachi branch of TiE. <s> During the late hours of 24 April 2015, Mahmud, while traveling in her Suzuki Swift (registration Number AWH 541), was fatally shot by gunmen near the DHA library on her way home after hosting a seminar. <s> As her car stopped at a red light less than 500 metres to the north of T2F, Saad Aziz who was riding a motorcycle driven by Aliur Rehman aka Tony rode up alongside it and shot Mahmud, who was in the driving seat, four or five times with a 9mm gun.
simple: Sabeen Mahmud was a Pakistani human rights activist and social NGO worker. <s> She was the founder and director of the Karachi-based cafe The Second Floor (T2F) and president of the Karachi branch of TiE. <s> On 24 April 2015, she was shot dead by unidentified gunmen in Karachi while on her way home after attending a seminar.

title: Piet Steenkamp
complex: Petrus Antonius Josephus Maria "Piet" Steenkamp (8 March 1925 – 8 January 2016) was a Dutch politician of the Christian Democratic Appeal (CDA) party. <s> He played an important role in the formation of the party and is therefore referred to as the father of the CDA. <s> He was president of the Dutch Senate from 1983 to 1991. <s> He was succeeded by Herman Tjeenk Willink. <s> He died in Eindhoven, Noord-Brabant on 8 January 2016, 90 years old.
simple: Petrus Antonius Josephus Maria "Piet" Steenkamp (8 March 1925 – 8 January 2016) was a Dutch politician and economist. <s> He was a member of the Christian Democratic Appeal (CDA), which he co-founded. <s> He was President of the Senate from 1983 to 1991. <s> Steenkamp died on 8 January 2016 in Eindhoven, North Brabant, aged 90.

title: László Sólyom
complex: László Sólyom ( , ] ; born 3 January 1942) is a Hungarian political figure, lawyer, and librarian who was President of Hungary from 2005 until 2010. <s> Previously he was president of the Constitutional Court of Hungary from 1990 to 1998.
simple: László Sólyom (, ]; born 3 January 1942) is a Hungarian politician, lawyer, and librarian. <s> He was the President of Hungary from 2005 until 2010.

title: Gnat
complex: A gnat is any of many species of tiny flying insects in the dipterid suborder Nematocera, especially those in the families Mycetophilidae, Anisopodidae and Sciaridae. <s> They can be both biting and non-biting. <s> Most often they fly in large numbers, called clouds. <s> "Gnat" is a loose descriptive category rather than a phylogenetic or other technical term, so there is no scientific consensus on what constitutes a gnat. <s> Some entomologists consider only non-biting flies to be gnats. <s> Certain universities also distinguish eye gnats: the Smithsonian Institution describes them as "non-biting flies, no bigger than a few grains of salt, ... attracted to fluids secreted by your eyes".
simple: A gnat is any tiny fly in the suborder Nematocera. <s> They can be both biting and non-biting. <s> Often they fly in large numbers, called clouds, in damp places like the Scottish Highlands. <s> "Gnat" is a loose descriptive category rather than a technical term. <s> the Smithsonian Institution describes them as “non-biting flies, no bigger than a few grains of salt, ... attracted to fluids secreted by your eyes”.

title: Lauren Hutton
complex: Mary Laurence "Lauren" Hutton (born November 17, 1943) is an American model and actress. <s> Raised in the southern United States, Hutton relocated to New York City in her early adulthood to begin a modeling career.
simple: Lauren Hutton (born November 17 1943, Charleston, South Carolina) is an American fashion model and actress who appeared on the cover of "Vogue" magazine more than 20 times.

title: Sansha
complex: Sansha is a prefecture-level city of Hainan province of the People's Republic of China (PRC). <s> It is located on Woody Island and administers (actually or nominally) several island groups and undersea atolls in the South China Sea including the Spratly Islands, the Paracel Islands, Macclesfield Bank, Scarborough Shoal, and a number of other ungrouped maritime features. <s> The entire territory is disputed, and the PRC's "de facto" control over the area varies.
simple: Sansha (三沙) is a city of the People's Republic of China (PRC) in Hainan Province. <s> In 2012, the city was established to administer several uninhabited island groups and undersea atolls in the South China Sea, including the Spratly and Paracel Islands as well as the Macclesfield Bank.

title: Ancient Egyptian royal titulary
complex: The royal titulary or royal protocol is the standard naming convention taken by the pharaohs of ancient Egypt. <s> It symbolises worldly power and holy might and also acts as a sort of mission statement for the reign of a monarch (sometimes it even changed during the reign). <s> The full titulary, consisting of five names, did not come into standard usage until the Middle Kingdom but remained in use as late as the Roman Empire. <s> G5-O33 The Horus name is the oldest form of the pharaoh's name, originating in prehistoric Egypt. <s> Many of the oldest-known Egyptian pharaohs were known only by this title. <s> The Horus name was usually written in a serekh, a representation of a palace façade. <s> The name of the pharaoh was written in hieroglyphs inside this representation of a palace. <s> Typically an image of the falcon god Horus was perched on top of or beside it. <s> At least one Egyptian ruler, the Second Dynasty pharoah Seth-Peribsen, used an image of the god Set instead of Horus, perhaps signifying an internal religious division within the country. <s> He was succeeded by Khasekhemwy, who placed the symbols of both Set and Horus above his name. <s> Thereafter, the image of Horus always appeared alongside the name of the pharaoh. <s> By the time of the New Kingdom, the Horus name was often written without the enclosing serekh. <s> The name is triumph of Horus over his uncle Seth, as the symbol for gold can be taken to mean that Horus was "superior to his foes". <s> Gold also was strongly associated in the ancient Egyptian mind with eternity, so this may have been intended to convey the pharaoh's eternal Horus name. <s> Similar to the Nebty name, this particular name typically was not framed by a cartouche or serekh. <s> The name itself was preceded by the title "Son of Ra", written with the hieroglyph of a duck ("za"), a homonym for the word meaning "son" ("za"), adjacent to an image of the sun, a hieroglyph for the chief solar deity Ra. <s> It was first introduced to the set of royal titles in the Fourth Dynasty and emphasizes the king's role as a representative of the solar god Ra. <s> For women who became pharaoh, the preceding title was interpreted as "daughter" also. <s> Modern historians typically refer to the ancient kings of Egypt by this name, adding ordinals (e.g. "II", "III") to distinguish between different individuals bearing the same name.

title: Benigno Aquino Jr.
complex: Benigno Simeon "Ninoy" Aquino Jr. (November 27, 1932 – August 21, 1983) was a Filipino politician who served as a Senator of the Philippines (1967–1972) and governor of the province of Tarlac. <s> He was the husband of former Philippine President Corazon Aquino and father of former Philippine President Benigno Aquino III. <s> Aquino, together with Gerardo Roxas and Jovito Salonga, formed the leadership of the opposition towards then President Ferdinand Marcos. <s> Shortly after the imposition of martial law, he was arrested in 1972 along with others associated with the Communists' armed insurgency and incarcerated for seven years. <s> He founded his own party, Lakas ng Bayan, and ran in the 1978 Philippine parliamentary election, but all of the party's candidates, including Aquino, lost in the election. <s> In 1980, Aquino was permitted by Marcos to travel to the United States for medical treatment following a heart attack. <s> He was assassinated at the Manila International Airport in 1983 upon returning from his self-imposed exile. <s> His death catapulted his widow, Corazon, into the political limelight, and prompted her to successfully run for a six-year term as President as a member of the UNIDO party in the 1986 snap election.
simple: Benigno Kheng Hon "Ninoy" Aquino, Jr. was a Filipino senator and a former Governor of Tarlac. <s> He was born on November 27, 1932 and died on August 21, 1983 at the age of 50. <s> Aquino, Gerry Roxas and Jovito Salonga formed the leadership of the opposition to the government of President Ferdinand Marcos. <s> Shortly after that, he was arrested in 1973 for seven years. <s> Aquino was allowed to travel to the United States for medical treatment following a heart attack. <s> He was killed at the Manila International Airport in 1983 upon returning from his self-imposed exile. <s> Aquino's death caused his widow, Corazon Aquino, to run for President in 1986.

title: Golden eagle
complex: The golden eagle ("Aquila chrysaetos") is one of the best-known birds of prey in the Northern Hemisphere. <s> It is the most widely distributed species of eagle. <s> Like all eagles, it belongs to the family Accipitridae. <s> These birds are dark brown, with lighter golden-brown plumage on their napes. <s> Immature eagles of this species typically have white on the tail and often have white markings on the wings. <s> Golden eagles use their agility and speed combined with powerful feet and massive, sharp talons to snatch up a variety of prey, mainly hares, rabbits, and marmots and other ground squirrels. <s> Once widespread across the Holarctic, it has disappeared from many areas which are now more heavily populated by humans. <s> Despite being extirpated from or uncommon in some of its former range, the species is still widespread, being present in sizeable stretches of Eurasia, North America, and parts of North Africa. <s> It is the largest and least populous of the five species of true accipitrid to occur as a breeding species in both the Palearctic and the Nearctic.
simple: The golden eagle ("Aquila chrysaetos") is one of the best-known birds of prey in the northern hemisphere. <s> It is the most widely distributed species of eagle. <s> Like all eagles, it belongs to the family Accipitridae. <s> Golden eagles use their agility and speed combined with powerful feet and massive, sharp talons to snatch up prey. <s> They eat hares, rabbits, marmots and other ground squirrels. <s> Once common across the Holarctic, it has gone from many areas heavily populated by humans. <s> The species is still widespread. <s> It lives in Eurasia, North America, and parts of North Africa.

title: Bombyliidae
complex: The Bombyliidae are a family of flies. <s> Their common name are bee flies or humbleflies. <s> Adults generally feed on nectar and pollen, some being important pollinators. <s> Larvae generally are parasitoids of other insects. <s> The Bombyliidae are a large family of flies comprising hundreds of genera, but the lifecycles of most species are known poorly, or not at all. <s> They range in size from very small (2 mm in length) to very large for flies (wingspan of some 40 mm). <s> When at rest, many species hold their wings at a characteristic "swept back" angle. <s> Adults generally feed on nectar and pollen, some being important pollinators, often with spectacularly long probosces adapted to plants such as "Lapeirousia" species with very long, narrow floral tubes. <s> Unlike butterflies, bee flies hold their proboscis straight, and cannot retract it. <s> In parts of East Anglia, locals refer to them as beewhals, thanks to their tusk-like appendages. <s> Many Bombyliidae superficially resemble bees and accordingly the prevalent common name for a member of the family is bee fly. <s> Possibly the resemblance is Batesian mimicry, affording the adults some protection from predators. <s> The larval stages are predators or parasitoids of the eggs and larvae of other insects. <s> The adult females usually deposit eggs in the vicinity of possible hosts, quite often in the burrows of beetles or wasps/solitary bees. <s> Although insect parasitoids usually are fairly host-specific, often highly host-specific, some Bombyliidae are opportunistic and will attack a variety of hosts. <s> The Bombyliidae include at least 4,500 described species, and certainly thousands more remain to be described.
simple: The Bombyliidae are a family of flies. <s> Their common name is bee flies. <s> The Bombyliidae are a large family of flies. <s> It has hundreds of genera, but the life cycles of most species are known poorly, or not at all. <s> The Bombyliidae include a large number of species, but for its size this is one of the least understood families of insects. <s> Some are very small (2 mm in length), but some can be very large for flies (wingspan of some 40 mm). <s> Adults normally feed on nectar and pollen. <s> Those with a spectacularly long proboscis are adapted to plants (such as "Lapeirousia") which have long, narrow floral tubes. <s> The adult flies usually feed on nectar and pollen, and some are important pollinators. <s> Many Bombyliidae look like bees and so a common name for the family is the bee flies. <s> The larval stages are predators or parasitoids of the eggs and larvae of other insects. <s> The adult females usually lay eggs near the nests of possible hosts, often in the burrows of solitary bees, wasps or beetles. <s> Although most bee-flies usually are fairly or highly host-specific, some species do attack a number of hosts.

title: Gwen (given name)
complex: Gwen is a Welsh feminine given name meaning "white, holy".
simple: The name Gwen is a female given name of Welsh origin. <s> It means "white, holy".

title: Jan Matsys
complex: Jan Massijs or Jan Matsys (c.1510 – 8 October 1575) was a Flemish Renaissance painter known for his history paintings, genre scenes and landscapes. <s> He also gained a reputation as a painter of the female nude, which he painted with a sensuality reminiscent of the school of Fontainebleau.
simple: Jan Massys (born around 1510 in Antwerp, died 8 October 1575, also in Antwerp) was a Flemish painter.

title: Nabi Şensoy
complex: Nabi Sensoy (25 May 1945, Istanbul – 7 February 2018, İzmir, Turkey) was the ambassador of Turkey to the United States. <s> He held that office beginning in January 2006. <s> He was recalled to Turkey in October 2007 after the United States House Committee on Foreign Affairs passed a resolution condemning the Armenian Genocide in the Ottoman Empire. <s> He returned to his position shortly afterwards. <s> He resigned in December of 2009.
simple: Nabi Şensoy (May 25, 1945 – February 7, 2018) was a Turkish politician. <s> He was the Ambassador of Turkey to the United States. <s> Şensoy died on February 7, 2018 in in İzmir, Turkey at the age of 73. <s> Şensoy held that office beginning in January 2006. <s> He was recalled to Turkey in October 2007 after the United States criticized Turkey for the Armenian Genocide in the Ottoman Empire. <s> He returned to his position shortly afterwards. <s> Şensoy resigned in December of 2009.

title: Lung tumor
complex: "Lung tumors" are neoplastic lung nodules.
simple: Lung tumors are tumors that grow in the lungs. <s> Some of the tumors are cancer.

title: Sabu (wrestler)
complex: Terry Michael Brunk (born December 12, 1964) is an American professional wrestler, better known by his ring name Sabu. <s> He currently wrestles on the independent circuit, most recently for Impact Wrestling. <s> He is known for his hardcore wrestling style, which he pioneered in his time with Extreme Championship Wrestling (ECW) from 1995 to 2000. <s> He is also known for his work in World Wrestling Entertainment (WWE) from 2006 to 2007, where he wrestled on the rebooted ECW brand as an "ECW Original". <s> Brunk was trained by his uncle, Ed Farhat (The Sheik), and was initially trained to be a technical wrestler. <s> He began his wrestling career in 1985 in Farhat's promotion, Big Time Wrestling, and was billed as being from Saudi Arabia under the ring names "Sabu the Elephant Boy" (use of "The Elephant Boy" was later dropped) and "Terry S.R." (the "S.R." standing for "Sheik's Revenge").
simple: Terry Michael Brunk (born December 12, 1964) is an American professional wrestler. <s> He is known for competing in hardcore-type matches. <s> He was trained by his uncle, Ed Farhat who was known by his ring name, The Sheik.

title: Phelps County, Nebraska
complex: Phelps County is a county in the U.S. state of Nebraska. <s> As of the 2010 United States Census, the population was 9,188. <s> Its county seat is Holdrege. <s> The county was formed in 1873, and was named for William Phelps, an early settler.
simple: Phelps County is a county in the U.S. state of Nebraska. <s> As of the 2010 census, 9,188 people lived there. <s> The county seat is Holdrege. <s> It was founded in 1873.

title: Limbourg brothers
complex: The Limbourg brothers ( ; fl. 1385 – 1416) were famous Dutch miniature painters (Herman, Paul, and Johan) from the city of Nijmegen. <s> They were active in the early 15th century in France and Burgundy, working in the style known as International Gothic. <s> They created what is certainly the best-known late medieval illuminated manuscript, the "Très Riches Heures du Duc de Berry".
simple: The Limbourg brothers, or in Dutch "Gebroeders van Limburg" (Herman, Paul, and Johan; fl. 1385 – 1416), were famous Dutch Renaissance miniature painters from the city of Nijmegen. <s> They were active in the early 15th century in France and Burgundy. <s> They created what is certainly the best known late medieval illuminated manuscript, "Les Très Riches Heures du Duc de Berry".

title: André Ramalho
complex: André Ramalho Silva (born 16 February 1992) is a footballer who plays as a centre-back for Red Bull Salzburg.
simple: André Ramalho Silva (born 16 February 1992) is a football player from Brazil.

title: Alan Rabinowitz
complex: Alan Robert Rabinowitz (December 31, 1953 – August 5, 2018) was an American zoologist who served as the President, CEO, and chief scientist at Panthera Corporation, a nonprofit conservation organization devoted to protecting the world's 40 wild cat species. <s> Called the "Indiana Jones of Wildlife Protection" by "Time", he studied jaguars, clouded leopards, Asiatic leopards, tigers, Sumatran rhinos, bears, leopard cats, raccoons, and civets. <s> Rabinowitz was diagnosed with chronic lymphocytic leukemia in 2001. <s> He died on August 5, 2018 from the progression of his cancer. <s> Conservation magazine "Conjour" said he left behind a "legacy of inspirational big cat conservation".
simple: Alan Robert Rabinowitz (December 31, 1953 – August 5, 2018) was an American zoologist. <s> He was the chief scientist at Panthera Corporation, a nonprofit conservation organization devoted to protecting the world's 40 wild cat species. <s> He was called the "Indiana Jones of Wildlife Protection" by "Time". <s> He studied jaguars, clouded leopards, Asiatic leopards, tigers, Sumatran rhinos, bears, leopard cats, raccoons, and civets. <s> On August 5, 2018, Rabinowitz died from leukemia in Manhattan, aged 64.

title: Botanical name
complex: A botanical name is a formal scientific name conforming to the "International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants" (ICN) and, if it concerns a plant cultigen, the additional cultivar or Group epithets must conform to the "International Code of Nomenclature for Cultivated Plants" (ICNCP). <s> The code of nomenclature covers "all organisms traditionally treated as algae, fungi, or plants, whether fossil or non-fossil, including blue-green algae (Cyanobacteria), chytrids, oomycetes, slime moulds and photosynthetic protists with their taxonomically related non-photosynthetic groups (but excluding Microsporidia)." <s> The purpose of a formal name is to have a single name that is accepted and used worldwide for a particular plant or plant group. <s> For example, the botanical name "Bellis perennis" denotes a plant species which is native to most of the countries of Europe and the Middle East, where it has accumulated various names in many languages. <s> Later, the plant was introduced worldwide, bringing it into contact with more languages. <s> English names for this plant species include: daisy, English daisy, and lawn daisy. <s> The cultivar "Bellis perennis" 'Aucubifolia' is a golden-variegated horticultural selection of this species. <s> A botanical name in three parts, i.e., an infraspecific name (a name for a taxon below the rank of species) needs a "connecting term" to indicate rank. <s> In the "Calystegia" example above, this is "subsp.", for subspecies. <s> In botany there are many ranks below that of species (in zoology there is only one such rank, subspecies, so that this "connecting term" is not used in zoology). <s> A name of a "subdivision of a genus" also needs a connecting term (in the "Acacia" example above, this is "subg.", <s> The connecting term is not part of the name itself. <s> For botanical nomenclature, the "ICN" prescribes a two-part name or binary name for any taxon below the rank of genus down to, and including the rank of species. <s> Taxa below the rank of species get a three part (infraspecific name). <s> A binary name consists of the name of a genus and an epithet.
simple: A botanical name is a formal scientific name which follows the "International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants" (ICN). <s> If it concerns a plant cultigen, the additional cultivar term must follow the "International Code of Nomenclature for Cultivated Plants". <s> The code of nomenclature covers "all organisms traditionally treated as plants, whether fossil or non-fossil, e.g. blue-green algae (Cyanobacteria); fungi, including chytrids, oomycetes, and slime moulds; photosynthetic protists and taxonomically related non-photosynthetic groups". <s> The purpose of a formal name is to have a single name which is accepted and used worldwide for a particular plant or plant group. <s> For example, the botanical name "Bellis perennis" was given to a plant species which is native to most of the countries of Europe and the Middle East, where it has various names in many languages. <s> Later it has been introduced worldwide, bringing it into contact with more languages. <s> Some English names for this plant species are: daisy, English daisy, lawndaisy. <s> The cultivar "Bellis perennis" 'Aucubifolia' is a golden-variegated horticultural selection of this species. <s> A name in three parts, i.e., an infraspecific name (a name for a taxon below the rank of species), needs a "connecting term" to indicate rank. <s> In the "Calystegia" example above, this is "subsp." (for subspecies). <s> In botany there are many ranks below that of species (in zoology there is only one such rank, subspecies, so that this "connecting term" is unnecessary there). <s> A name of a "subdivision of a genus" also needs a connecting term (in the "Acacia" example above, this is "subg.", <s> The connecting term is not part of the name itself. <s> For botanical nomenclature, the "ICBN" prescribes a two-part name or binary name for any taxon below the rank of genus down to, and including the rank of species. <s> Taxa below the rank of species get a three part name. <s> A binary name consists of the name of a genus and an epithet.

title: Kiruna Church
complex: Kiruna Church is a church building in Kiruna, Sweden, and is one of Sweden's largest wooden buildings. <s> The church exterior is built in a Gothic Revival style, while the altar is in Art Nouveau. <s> The church was built between 1909–1912, and consecrated by Bishop Olof Bergqvist on 8 December 1912. <s> Since 1913, the church is included in the Jukkasjärvi parish in the diocese of Luleå.
simple: Kiruna Church is a church building in the town of Kiruna in Sweden. <s> It was opened on 8 December 1912 by bishop Olof Bergqvist.

title: Joel Hastings Metcalf
complex: Joel Hastings Metcalf (January 4, 1866 – February 23, 1925) was an American astronomer, humanitarian and minister. <s> Reverend Metcalf graduated from Harvard Divinity School in 1892. <s> He served as a Unitarian minister in Burlington, Vermont and in Taunton, Massachusetts, Winchester, Massachusetts and Portland, Maine. <s> He discovered or co-discovered several comets, including 23P/Brorsen-Metcalf and 97P/Metcalf-Brewington, and also 41 asteroids during 1905–1914, as credited by the Minor Planet Center.
simple: Joel Hastings Metcalf (January 4, 1866–February 23, 1925) was an American astronomer. <s> Metcalf graduated from Harvard Divinity School in 1892. <s> He served as a Unitarian minister in Burlington, Vermont and then later in Taunton, Massachusetts, Winchester, Massachusetts and Portland, Maine. <s> He found or co-found many comets, such as 23P/Brorsen-Metcalf and 97P/Metcalf-Brewington; he also found many asteroids.

title: Riemann sphere
complex: In mathematics, the Riemann sphere, named after Bernhard Riemann, is a model of the extended complex plane, the complex plane plus a point at infinity. <s> This extended plane represents the extended complex numbers, that is, the complex numbers plus a value ∞ for infinity. <s> With the Riemann model, the point "∞" is near to very large numbers, just as the point "0" is near to very small numbers. <s> The extended complex numbers are useful in complex analysis because they allow for division by zero in some circumstances, in a way that makes expressions such as formula_1 well-behaved. <s> For example, any rational function on the complex plane can be extended to a holomorphic function on the Riemann sphere, with the poles of the rational function mapping to infinity. <s> More generally, any meromorphic function can be thought of as a holomorphic function whose codomain is the Riemann sphere. <s> In geometry, the Riemann sphere is the prototypical example of a Riemann surface, and is one of the simplest complex manifolds. <s> In projective geometry, the sphere can be thought of as the complex projective line P(C), the projective space of all complex lines in C.
simple: The Riemann sphere is a mathematical model of the extended complex plane. <s> The model is named after Bernhard Riemann. <s> The extended complex plane is the plane of the complex numbers, plus a point at infinity. <s> With this model, this point at infinity is "close" to very large numbers in the same way zero is "close" to very small ones. <s> The extended complex numbers are useful for Complex analysis: in certain cases, the division by zero is "well-behaved", in the sense that dividing by zero gives this point at infinity. <s> In geometry, the Riemann sphere is a simple example of a Riemann surface. <s> It is also one of the simplest complex manifolds.

title: Chikugo, Fukuoka
complex: Chikugo (筑後市 , Chikugo-shi ) is a city located in Fukuoka Prefecture, Japan. <s> The city was founded on April 1, 1954.
simple: Chikugo (筑後市, Chikugo-shi) is a Japanese city in Fukuoka Prefecture on the island of Kyushu. <s> The city of Chikugo is near Kurume, Fukuoka.

title: Peter MacGregor-Scott
complex: Peter MacGregor-Scott (December 28, 1947 – October 29, 2017) was a British film producer, production manager and assistant director. <s> He produced the 1997 film "Batman & Robin". <s> He also produced the Cheech & Chong films "Cheech & Chong's The Corsican Brothers", "Still Smokin" and "Born in East L.A.". <s> Others are "The Whoopee Boys" and "Death to Smoochy". <s> Peter MacGregor-Scott was born in Maidenhead, England. <s> His father was J. C. MacGregor Scott, who served as an executive with such British film companies as Columbia Pictures U.K., Warner-Pathe Distributors and Commonwealth United International. <s> He is survived by his two children, Elizabeth Kennedy ("née" MacGregor-Scott), Taylor MacGregor-Scott and his wife, Susan ("née" Brustien) MacGregor-Scott. <s> MacGregor-Scott was involved in a taxi accident in New York City which resulted in complications which would lead to his death on October 25, 2017, aged 69.
simple: Peter MacGregor-Scott (December 28, 1947 – October 25, 2017) was an American movie producer. <s> He produced the 1997 movie, "Batman & Robin". <s> He also produced the Cheech & Chong movie "Cheech & Chong's The Corsican Brothers", "Still Smokin" and "Born in East L.A.". <s> Others are "The Whoopee Boys" and "Death to Smoochy". <s> He was born in Maidenhead, Berkshire, England. <s> MacGregor-Scott was involved in a traffic collision in New York City which would result in his death on October 25, 2017, aged 69.

title: Kyriakos Mitsotakis
complex: Kyriakos Mitsotakis ( ; born 4 March 1968) is a Greek politician serving as Prime Minister of Greece since 2019. <s> A member of New Democracy, he has been its president since 2016. <s> Mitsotakis previously was Leader of the Opposition from 2016 to 2019 and Minister of Administrative Reform from 2013 to 2015. <s> He was first elected to the Hellenic Parliament for the Athens B constituency in 2004. <s> After New Democracy suffered two election defeats in 2015, he was elected the party's leader in January 2016. <s> Three years later, on 7 July 2019, he led his party to a majority in the 2019 election, their first since 2007. <s> He is the son of former Prime Minister Konstantinos Mitsotakis. <s> During the 2000 legislative election, Mitsotakis worked for New Democracy's national campaign.
simple: Kyriakos Mitsotakis (; born 4 March 1968) is a Greek politician. <s> He became Prime Minister of Greece on 8 July 2019. <s> He served as Minister of Administrative Reform from 2013 to 2015. <s> Mitsotakis has been a member of the Hellenic Parliament since 2004. <s> He is the son of former Prime Minister Konstantinos Mitsotakis.

title: Mariem Hassan
complex: Mariem Hassan ( ‎; May 1958 – 22 August 2015) was a Sahrawi singer and lyricist from Western Sahara. <s> She usually sang in Hassaniyya, an Arabic dialect spoken mostly in Western Sahara and Mauritania, and occasionally in Spanish. <s> Her use of the Spanish language was related to the former status of Western Sahara as a Spanish colony. <s> Hassan died of bone cancer in the Sahrawi refugee camps of Tindouf province, Algeria on 22 August 2015.
simple: Mariem Hassan (‎; 1958 – 22 August 2015), was a Sahrawi singer and lyricist from Western Sahara. <s> She usually sang in Hassaniyya, an Arabic dialect spoken mostly in Western Sahara and Mauritania. <s> Hassan died of bone cancer in a Sahrawi refugee camp in Tindouf, Algeria on 22 August 2015.

title: Corps of Guides (India)
complex: The Corps of Guides was a regiment of the British Army (India) made up of white British officers and Indian lower ranks to serve on the North West Frontier. <s> As originally raised in 1846, The Guides consisted of infantry and cavalry. <s> It evolved through the 20th century to become the Guides Cavalry and Guides Infantry. <s> Once independence was granted to India and after the partition, The Guides were given over to Pakistan and became part of the Pakistan Army with all ranks including officers being recruited solely from Pakistan. <s> The brainchild of Sir Henry Lawrence, the Corps had Lt. Harry Lumsden as its commandant and W.S.R. Hodson (the Hodson of "Hodson's Horse") as second-in-command. <s> On 6 February 1847 Lumsden wrote to his father " I have just been nominated to raise the corps of Guides. <s> It will be the finest appointment in the country".
simple: The Corps of Guides was a regiment of the British Indian Army which was formed and served mostly in the North-West Frontier Province of British India. <s> Its infantry section was incorporated into the Frontier Force Regiment while its cavalry side became the Guides Cavalry. <s> After 1947 and the independence of Pakistan, the Guides regiment became part of the Pakistan Army. <s> The idea for raising such a body of troops was Sir Henry Lawrence's. <s> He appointed a young officer, Lt. Harry Lumsden as its commandant and on 6 February 1847 Lumsden took over his famous command.

simple: Toba Tek Singh District is a district in the Punjab province of Pakistan. <s> The city of Toba Tek Singh is the capital.

title: Winged Creatures (film)

title: Slovakia at the 2018 Winter Paralympics

title: Ambutrix
complex: Ambutrix (pronounced ɑ̃.by.t̪ʁiks) is a French commune in the Ain department in the Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes region of eastern France. <s> The inhabitants of the commune are known as "Butrians" or "Butrianes". <s> The commune takes its name from the presence of Celtic people called Ambarri in the region.
simple: Ambutrix is a commune. <s> It is found in the Auvergne-Rhône-Alpes region in the Ain department in the east of France. <s> The inhabitants are the "Butrians". <s> The name of the commune comes from a Celtic tribe which lived in the area called the "Ambarres".

title: British Rail Class 46
complex: The British Rail Class 46 is a class of diesel locomotive. <s> They were built from 1961–1963 at British Railways' Derby Works and were initially numbered D138–D193. <s> With the arrival of TOPS they were renumbered to Class 46. <s> Fifty-six locomotives were built. <s> The first was withdrawn in 1977 and all of them were withdrawn by the end of 1984. <s> The Class 46 design was structurally the same as the preceding Class 45 build, and had the same Sulzer engine, but differed in the fitment of a Brush generator and traction motors, in place of the Crompton Parkinson equipment fitted to the Class 45. <s> Along with the other Sulzer class 44 and 45 designs they are often referred to as "Peaks", so named because the earliest of the Class 44 were named after mountains.
simple: The British Rail Class 46 is a class of diesel locomotive. <s> They were built from 1961-1963 at British Railways' Derby Works and were initially numbered D138-D193. <s> With the arrival of TOPS computer system they were renumbered to Class 46. <s> Fifty-six locomotives were built. <s> The first was withdrawn in 1977 and all of them were withdrawn by 1984. <s> The Class 46 design was structurally the same as the earlier Class 45 build, and had the same Sulzer engine. <s> It differed in the fitment of a Brush generator and traction motors, in place of the Crompton Parkinson equipment fitted to the Class 45.

title: William Bennett
complex: William John Bennett (born July 31, 1943) is an American conservative pundit, politician, and political theorist, who served as Secretary of Education from 1985 to 1988 under President Ronald Reagan. <s> He also held the post of Director of the Office of National Drug Control Policy under George H. W. Bush. <s> Bennett was born July 31, 1943 in Brooklyn, the son of Nancy ("née" Walsh), a medical secretary, and F. Robert Bennett, a banker. <s> He moved to Washington, D.C., where he attended Gonzaga College High School. <s> He graduated from Williams College, where he was a member of the Kappa Alpha Society, and went on to earn a Ph.D. from the University of Texas at Austin in Political Philosophy. <s> He also has a J.D. from Harvard Law School.
simple: William John "Bill" Bennett (born July 31, 1943) is an American politician. <s> He was the third United States Secretary of Education. <s> He served from February 1985 through September 1988. <s> From 1989 to 1990, he served as the first Director of the Office of National Drug Control Policy. <s> Bennett was born in Brooklyn, New York. <s> He studied at Williams College, at the University of Texas-Austin, and at Harvard Law School.

title: Condette
complex: Condette is a commune in the Pas-de-Calais department in the Hauts-de-France region of France.
simple: Condette is a commune. <s> It is found in the region Nord-Pas-de-Calais in the Pas-de-Calais department in the north of France.

title: Trochophore
complex: A trochophore ( ; also spelled trocophore) is a type of free-swimming planktonic marine larva with several bands of cilia. <s> By moving their cilia rapidly, a water eddy is created. <s> In this way they control the direction of their movement. <s> Additionally, in this way they bring their food closer, in order to capture it more easily.
simple: A trochophore is a type of larva found in marine plankton. <s> By moving their cilia rapidly, a water eddy is created. <s> In this way they control the direction of their movement. <s> Also, in this way they bring their food closer, to capture it more easily.

title: Jeet Gayi Toh Piya Morey (TV series)
complex: Jeet Gayi Toh Piya Morey (English: If I win then, O Beloved, you're mine) is an Indian Hindi romantic drama television series, which premiered on 21 August 2017 and is broadcast on Zee TV. <s> The series is produced by Jay Production of Jay Mehta. <s> The series ended on 23 July 2018.
simple: Jeet Gayi Toh Piya Morey is an Indian Hindi romantic drama television series that premiered on 21 August 2017 and airs on Zee TV. <s> The series is produced by Jay Production .

title: Bismuth(III) sulfide
complex: Bismuth(III) sulfide is a chemical compound of bismuth and sulfur. <s> It occurs in nature as the mineral bismuthinite.
simple: Bismuth(III) sulfide, also known as bismuth sulfide, is a chemical compound. <s> It has bismuth and sulfide ions in it. <s> Bismuth(III) sulfide is a brown solid. <s> It is made by reacting hydrogen sulfide with a bismuth compound like bismuth(III) chloride. <s> It is found as the mineral bismuthinite.

title: Yoshi's Story
complex: Yoshi's Story is a side-scrolling platform game published and developed by Nintendo for the Nintendo 64. <s> It was first released in Japan in December 1997, and worldwide the following year. <s> It was re-released on the Wii's Virtual Console service in 2007, and later for the Wii U's Virtual Console in 2016. <s> Serving as a follow up to the Super NES title "Yoshi's Island", the game continues within the platform genre, presenting gameplay similar to its predecessor. <s> However, "Yoshi's Story" turns in a more puzzle-oriented direction, with the aspect of challenge being foremost tied to the achievement of a high score by strategic means. <s> Taking place within a pop-up storybook, the game features vivid pre-rendered 3D graphics, illustrating worlds that are crafted from different materials, such as cardboard, fabrics, plastic, and wood. <s> On each course, the goal is to fill the Fruit Frame by eating 30 pieces of fruit. <s> These may be found in abundance throughout every course, lying around, floating in bubbles, and even carried by some enemies. <s> The player can choose to eat everything they come across on their path.
simple: Yoshi's Story is a platform video game for the Nintendo 64 game console. <s> It was developed and published by Nintendo. <s> It was released in Japan on December 21, 1997, in North America on March 10, 1998, and in Europe on May 10, 1998. <s> It was later released for the Wii's Virtual Console service in 2007. <s> The game takes place in a pop-up book. <s> Each world is made from a different material, such as cardboard, fabric, plastic, and wood. <s> The goal in each stage is to fill the Fruit Frame by collecting 30 pieces of fruit. <s> They can be found lying on the stage, floating in bubbles, or carried by enemies.

title: William John Wills
complex: William John Wills (5 January 1834 – 28 June 1861 ) was a British surveyor who also trained as a surgeon. <s> Wills achieved fame as the second-in-command of the ill-fated Burke and Wills expedition, which was the first expedition to cross Australia from south to north, finding a route across the continent from the settled areas of Victoria to the Gulf of Carpentaria. <s> William John Wills was born on 5 January 1834 in Totnes, Devon, England, and he was the second of seven children born to William Wills (died 28 September 1889) and Sarah Mary Elizabeth Wills (née Calley, born 23 December 1800, baptized 12 March 1801 in Totnes, and died 19 February 1880).
simple: William John Wills (1834—1861) was an English surveyor. <s> He became one of the first explorers to cross Australia from the south to the north. <s> The expedition became known as the Burke and Wills expedition. <s> He was born in Totnes, Devon.

title: Cuzieu, Ain
complex: Cuzieu is a commune in the Ain department in eastern France.
simple: Cuzieu is a commune.

title: The History of Rock and Roll
complex: The History of Rock & Roll is a US radio documentary on rock and roll music, originally syndicated in 1969. <s> One of the lengthiest documentaries of any medium (48 hours in the 1969 version, 52 hours each for the 1978 and 1981 versions), "The History of Rock & Roll" is a definitive history of the Rock and Roll genre, stretching from the early 1950s to its day. <s> The "rockumentary," as producers Bill Drake and Gene Chenault called it, features hundreds of interviews and comments from numerous rock artists and people involved with rock and roll. <s> "The History of Rock & Roll" first aired on the weekend of February 21–23, 1969 on 93 KHJ Los Angeles, hosted by Robert W. Morgan. <s> It aired for 48 hours and was later syndicated.
simple: The History of Rock & Roll was a radio documentary on rock and roll music. <s> It was first broadcast in 1969. <s> "The History of Rock & Roll" told the story of Rock and Roll music from the early 1950s to its day. <s> In the fall of 1969 many other stations broadcast this documentary. <s> The 1969 version was 48 hours long. <s> The 1978 version was 52 hours long. <s> Producers Bill Drake and Gene Chenault called this a "rockumentary". <s> Los Angeles radio station KHJ first broadcast this show on February 21-23, 1969.

title: Ya'akov Nehoshtan
complex: Ya'akov Nehoshtan (Hebrew: יעקב נחושתן ‎; 22 April 1925 – 17 April 2019) was an Israeli politician and diplomat. <s> He served as a member of the Knesset for Gahal between 1969 and 1974 and as ambassador to the Netherlands between 1982 and 1985. <s> Born in Kazanlak, Bulgaria, Nehoshtan attended high school in Vratsa and was a member of the Hashomer Hatzair youth group. <s> He made aliyah to Mandatory Palestine in 1944, and studied law at the Hebrew University of Jerusalem, gaining certification as a lawyer. <s> He joined the Irgun in 1944, and was arrested by the British authorities the following year and exiled to a detention camp in Eritrea. <s> In 1947 he was moved to a camp in Kenya. <s> In 1979 he was appointed Deputy Chief of Mission at the Embassy of Israel in Washington, D.C. and in 1982 became ambassador to the Netherlands, a post he held until 1985. <s> His son, Ido, served as commander of the Israeli Air Force.
simple: Ya'akov Nehoshtan (Hebrew: יעקב נחושתן‎; 22 April 1925 – 17 April 2019) was an Israeli politician, diplomat and lawyer. <s> Nehoshtan died on 17 April 2019, at the age of 93. <s> He served as a member of the Knesset for Gahal between 1969 and 1974. <s> He also served as Israeli Ambassador to the Netherlands between 1982 and 1985. <s> Nehoshtan was born in Kazanlak, Bulgaria. <s> He fled to Mandatory Palestine in 1944. <s> His son, Ido, served as commander of the Israeli Air Force.

title: Georgi Atanasov (politician)
complex: Georgi Ivanov Atanasov (Bulgarian: Георги Иванов Атанасов) (born 25 July 1933) was a leading member of the Bulgarian Communist Party who served as Prime Minister from 1986-1990. <s> Atanasov supported the move to oust Todor Zhivkov as Chairman of the State Council, joining Petar Mladenov in leading the opposition. <s> In November 1992 he was sentenced to ten years imprisonment for embezzlement, although he was pardoned in 1994.
simple: Georgi Ivanov Atanasov (Bulgarian: Георги Иванов Атанасов) (born 25 July 1933) is a Bulgarian politician and military official. <s> He was a leading member of the Bulgarian Communist Party. <s> He was Prime Minister from 1986 to 1990. <s> Atanasov supported the move to oust Todor Zhivkov as Chairman of the State Council.

title: Perlin noise
complex: Perlin noise is a type of gradient noise developed by Ken Perlin in 1983 as a result of his frustration with the "machine-like" look of computer graphics at the time. <s> He formally described his findings in a SIGGRAPH paper in 1985 called "An image Synthesizer".
simple: Perlin noise was made by Ken Perlin in 1983.

title: Frauen-Bundesliga
complex: The Frauen-Bundesliga (English: Women's Federal League), currently known as the FLYERALARM Frauen-Bundesliga due to sponsorship by FLYERALARM, is the top level of league competition for women's association football in Germany. <s> In 1990 the German Football Association (DFB) created the German Women's Bundesliga, based on the model of the men's Bundesliga.
simple: The Frauen-Bundesliga (English: Women Bundesliga) is the main women's association football league competition in Germany.

title: Jerauld County, South Dakota
complex: Jerauld County is a county in the U.S. state of South Dakota. <s> As of the 2010 census, the population was 2,071. <s> Its county seat is Wessington Springs.
simple: Jerauld County is a county located in the U.S. state of South Dakota. <s> As of the 2010 census, 2,071 people lived there. <s> Its county seat is Wessington Springs.

title: Ian Wachtmeister
complex: Count Ian Melcher Shering Wachtmeister af Johannishus (] ; 24 December 1932 – 11 November 2017) was a Swedish industrialist and politician. <s> He was a member of the Swedish Riksdag from 1991 to 1994. <s> He was the son of Count Ted Wachtmeister and Adrienne, "née" De Geer. <s> Together with record company owner Bert Karlsson he founded the populist political party "New Democracy", and as party leader achieved parliamentary representation in the 1991 general election from Örebro County. <s> The party's criticism of the Swedish immigration politics generated accusations of racism. <s> Wachtmeister left the party in April 1994. <s> He died of cancer on 11 November 2017.
simple: Count Ian Melcher Shering Wachtmeister af Johannishus (]; 24 December 1932 – 11 November 2017) was a Swedish businessman and politician. <s> He was a member of the Swedish Riksdag from 1991 to 1994. <s> Together with record company owner Bert Karlsson he founded the populist political party "New Democracy", and as party leader achieved parliamentary representation in the 1991 general election from Örebro County. <s> Wachtmeister died of lymphoma on 11 November 2017 in Stockholm, Sweden at the age of 84.

title: Thomas Müller
complex: Thomas Müller (] ; born 13 September 1989) is a German professional footballer who plays for and vice-captains Bayern Munich, and has made 100 appearances for the German national team. <s> A versatile player, Müller plays as a midfielder or forward, and has been deployed in a variety of attacking roles – as an attacking midfielder, second striker, centre forward and on either wing. <s> He has been praised for his positioning, teamwork and stamina, work-rate, and has shown consistency in both scoring and creating goals. <s> Müller's role can be described as an attacking all-rounder, a player able to play in a variety of forward positions.
simple: Thomas Müller (born 13 September 1989) is a German football player. <s> He plays for FC Bayern Munich and Germany national team. <s> Müller can play as both a forward and midfielder. <s> Müller is known for his great positioning, team work and stamina.

title: Haarlem
complex: Haarlem (] ; predecessor of "Harlem" in the English language) is a city and municipality in the Netherlands. <s> It is the capital of the province of North Holland and is situated at the northern edge of the Randstad, one of the most populated metropolitan areas in Europe.
simple: Haarlem is a city in the Netherlands and the capital of the province North Holland.

simple: Lawrence County is a county in the U.S. state of Ohio. <s> In 2010, 62,450 people lived there. <s> The county seat is Ironton.

title: José Francisco Molina

simple: José Francisco Molina (born 8 August 1970) is a former Spanish football player.

title: Weston, McLean County, Illinois
complex: Weston is an unincorporated community located in McLean County, Illinois. <s> It currently is still in existence, as opposed to its now-defunct namesake in DuPage County. <s> Weston was laid out 26 August 1867 by W. F. Bryan. <s> The Original Town included 288 small lots, five blocks that were not subdivided and a Public Park. <s> The depot and town hall were on the south side of the tracks. <s> It was a station along the Toledo Peoria and Western Railroad. <s> In 1895 there were four churches. <s> Just east of town an area of natural tall grass prairie survives at Weston Cemetery Prairie.
simple: Weston, Illinois is an unincorporated community in McLean County, Illinois. <s> On 26 August 1867, W. F. Bryan laid out Weston. <s> The Original Town included 288 small lots, five blocks that were not subdivided and a Public Park. <s> The depot and town hall were on the south side of the tracks. <s> The station was for the Toledo Peoria and Western Railroad. <s> In 1895 there were four churches. <s> Just east of town, Western Cemetery has an area of natural tall grass prairie.

title: Venom (band)
complex: Venom are an English extreme metal band formed in 1978 in Newcastle upon Tyne. <s> Coming to prominence towards the end of the new wave of British heavy metal, Venom's first two albums—"Welcome to Hell" (1981) and "Black Metal" (1982)—are considered a major influence on thrash metal and extreme metal in general.
simple: Venom are a black metal band from Newcastle upon Tyne, England. <s> The band was formed in 1979.

title: Valery Bolotov
complex: Valery Dmitrievitch Bolotov (Russian: , ; 13 February 1970 – 27 January 2017) was a Ukrainian militant leader known for his involvement in the Donbass War in eastern Ukraine, and as the leader of the unrecognized Luhansk People's Republic. <s> Bolotov was found dead on 27 January 2017 in his own home in Moscow, Russia. <s> The causes of his death are currently being investigated.

title: St. Gallen (Wahlkreis)

simple: St. Gallen is a district of the canton of St. Gallen in Switzerland.

title: Butch Hartman
complex: Elmer Earl "Butch" Hartman IV (born January 10, 1965) is an American animator, YouTuber, illustrator, and voice actor, best known for creating the Nicktoons "The Fairly OddParents", "Danny Phantom", "T.U.F.F. Puppy", and "Bunsen Is a Beast". <s> Hartman also owns a production company, Billionfold Inc., which he uses primarily to produce his shows. <s> Hartman was an executive producer on "The Fairly OddParents" for the entirety of its 16-year run. <s> Hartman was born in Highland Park, Michigan. <s> He received the nickname Butch as a young boy and continued to use the name professionally as an adult. <s> Hartman spent his childhood in Roseville, Michigan and his teenage years in New Baltimore, Michigan. <s> He graduated from Anchor Bay High School in New Baltimore in 1983. <s> and subsequently attended the California Institute of the Arts in Valencia, California. <s> While still attending CalArts, Hartman interned as an in-between animator on the Don Bluth film "An American Tail". <s> Shortly after graduating, he was hired as a character designer and storyboard artist for an unidentified "My Little Pony" animated series. <s> As he had no previous experience with storyboards, he was soon fired. <s> Afterwards, he found work with Ruby-Spears, where he worked on "It's Punky Brewster" and "Dink, the Little Dinosaur". <s> He was also a member of the video reference crew for the Disney film "Pocahontas". <s> In the early 1990s he was hired as an artist in the model department at Hanna-Barbera, and was eventually contacted by studio president Fred Seibert to make the shorts "Pfish and Chip" and "Gramps" for the "What a Cartoon! <s> Eventually, he became a writer, director and storyboard artist for several of the early Cartoon Network shows, including "Dexter's Laboratory", "Johnny Bravo", "Cow and Chicken" and "I Am Weasel". <s> After his contract with Hanna-Barbera expired, he went to work with Seibert on the "Oh Yeah! <s> Cartoons" show for Nickelodeon. <s> During his time working at Hanna-Barbera, he became friends with future "Family Guy" creator Seth MacFarlane. <s> The two would later go on to make the short "Zoomates" together for Oh Yeah! <s> The character Dr. Elmer Hartman in "Family Guy" was named after Hartman. <s> He also voiced various characters in the show's first few seasons. <s> His biggest success came in December 1997, when he created "The Fairly OddParents". <s> The series originally started out as a series of shorts on the anthology show, "Oh Yeah! <s> Eventually, Nickelodeon decided to pick the shorts up as a full series. <s> Premiering in 2001, the adapted series ended up becoming a huge hit, second only in the ratings to "SpongeBob SquarePants" (and it briefly even passed "SpongeBob"' s ratings). <s> Following the third "" crossover "The Jimmy-Timmy Power Hour 3: The Jerkinators", the series ceased production in 2006, but it was announced on Hartman's forum on February 2, 2007 that 20 more episodes would be produced; the 6th season of "Fairly OddParents" aired on February 18, 2008, starting with the 1-hour special "Fairly OddBaby". <s> From May 1, 2009 to May 3, 2009, the 3-part special "Wishology" aired; although that too was originally intended as a series finale, the series was renewed for another season. <s> A tenth season was eventually ordered in 2015. <s> "The Fairly OddParents" is Nickelodeon's second longest-running animated show behind "SpongeBob". <s> Due to the success of "The Fairly OddParents", Hartman was asked to create another show for Nickelodeon; Hartman says the President of Nickelodeon asked him if he had an idea, and before he could say the title he was given the greenlight. <s> The show would later become "Danny Phantom". <s> To produce the show, in 2004, Hartman founded Billionfold Inc., which he also used, and still uses today, to produce his other projects. <s> "Danny Phantom" received critical acclaim and is considered Hartman's best show, with Hartman himself acknowledging it as perhaps the best of his programs. <s> "Danny Phantom" ended production in early 2007. <s> Around 2008–2009, Hartman began production his third show for Nickelodeon, "T.U.F.F. Puppy", which premiered in 2010 alongside the "Jimmy Neutron" spin-off "Planet Sheen". <s> The series received mixed to positive reviews and ran for 3 seasons before being cancelled. <s> After Hartman announced that he was leaving Nickelodeon, he said in the same video that he was working new projects to be released in the future. <s> He announced that he is working on a show called "Elf Detective" for his YouTube channel as well as multiple projects with PocketWatch, Inc. <s> On June 18, 2018, he launched a Kickstarter campaign for his own streaming service for family-focused entertainment called OAXIS. <s> It reached its goal of $250,000 on July 18, 2018. <s> His other TV work includes voicing various characters on the animated series "Family Guy" and playing the character Sean Masters on the short-lived series "Generations" in 1991. <s> He also appeared on the NBC soap opera "Days of Our Lives" during the late 1980s. <s> In 2012, it was announced that Hartman was set to serve as the director on the film adaptation of "ALF" for Sony Pictures Animation. <s> Hartman currently lives in Bell Canyon, California, with his wife, Julieann, and daughters, Carly and Sophia Hartman.
simple: Elmer Earl "Butch" Hartman IV (Born January 10, 1965, Highland Park, Michigan) is an American animator, creator of "The Fairly OddParents" and "Danny Phantom". <s> Hartman was born in Highland Park, Michigan to Elmer Earl Hartman III and Carol Davis. <s> He received the nickname "Butch" as a youth and continues to use the name professionally as an adult. <s> Hartman spent his childhood in PUPPY' set to premiere on Nickelodeon in October, 2010. <s> Hartman is currently working on two new projects for Nickelodeon: one, a live-action series and the other, animated. <s> His other TV work include voice actor|voicing various characters on the animated series "Family Guy" (the series' creator Seth MacFarlane even named the wacky family doctor Hartman after him), and playing the character Sean Masters on the short-lived series "Generations" in 1991. <s> He was also a recurring character on the popular NBC soap opera "Days of Our Lives" (1988 - 1989; see ). <s> Hartman currently lives in Bell Canyon, California, with his wife, Julieann, and daughters, Carly and Sophia.

title: Wilfredo Gómez
complex: Wilfredo Gómez Rivera (] ; born October 29, 1956), sometimes referred to as Bazooka Gómez, is a Puerto Rican former professional boxer and three-time world champion. <s> He is frequently mentioned among the best Puerto Rican boxers of all time by sports journalists and analysts, along with Félix Trinidad, Miguel Cotto, Wilfred Benítez, Esteban De Jesús, Edwin Rosario, and Carlos Ortíz.
